---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC"
  description="Privacy policy for Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC."
>
  <section class="bg-[#04163a] py-24 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
      <a
        href="/policies"
        class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-300 hover:text-blue-200"
      >
        ← Back to policies
      </a>

      <div class="mt-10 rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-8 sm:p-10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-blue-300">
          Wroughton & Wichelstowe FC
        </p>

        <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-light tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>

        <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-400">
          Last updated: May 2026
        </p>

        <div class="mt-12 space-y-12 text-slate-300">

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              1. Introduction
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              Wroughton & Wichelstowe Football Club (“WWFC”, “the Club”, “we”, “our” or “us”)
              is committed to protecting the privacy and security of personal information.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              This policy explains how we collect, use, store and protect personal data in
              accordance with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the
              Data Protection Act 2018.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              2. Information We Collect
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              We may collect and process the following types of personal information:
            </p>

            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6">
              <li>Player and parent/carer names</li>
              <li>Addresses, phone numbers and email addresses</li>
              <li>Emergency contact information</li>
              <li>Date of birth and age-group eligibility information</li>
              <li>Medical, accessibility or disability information where required for welfare and safeguarding</li>
              <li>FA registration and affiliation information</li>
              <li>Coach, volunteer and DBS information where applicable</li>
              <li>Attendance and participation records</li>
              <li>Website enquiry submissions</li>
              <li>Photos or videos where consent has been provided</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              3. How We Use Personal Information
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              Personal information is used to:
            </p>

            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6">
              <li>Administer football activities and registrations</li>
              <li>Communicate with players, parents, coaches and volunteers</li>
              <li>Manage safeguarding and welfare responsibilities</li>
              <li>Arrange fixtures, training and tournaments</li>
              <li>Support inclusion and accessibility requirements</li>
              <li>Meet obligations to leagues, County FAs and The FA</li>
              <li>Respond to enquiries submitted through the website</li>
              <li>Maintain club governance and operational records</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              4. Lawful Basis For Processing
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              We process personal information under one or more lawful bases including:
            </p>

            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6">
              <li>Consent</li>
              <li>Legitimate interests</li>
              <li>Legal obligations</li>
              <li>Vital interests relating to health, safeguarding and welfare</li>
              <li>Performance of a contract or participation agreement</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              5. Safeguarding & Sensitive Information
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              Some information relating to health, disability, welfare or safeguarding may be
              considered sensitive personal data.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              This information is handled with additional care and is only shared with authorised
              individuals where necessary to protect player welfare, safety and inclusion.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              6. Data Sharing
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              We may share information where necessary with:
            </p>

            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6">
              <li>The Football Association (FA)</li>
              <li>Wiltshire FA</li>
              <li>Football leagues and competition organisers</li>
              <li>Safeguarding or statutory authorities where legally required</li>
              <li>Approved service providers supporting club operations</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              We do not sell personal information to third parties.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              7. Data Retention
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              WWFC retains personal information only for as long as reasonably necessary
              for football administration, safeguarding, legal, insurance and regulatory purposes.
            </p>

            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6">
              <li>Player registration records are retained during active participation and for a limited period afterwards.</li>
              <li>Safeguarding records may be retained longer where required by FA safeguarding guidance.</li>
              <li>Financial and governance records are retained in accordance with legal obligations.</li>
              <li>Website enquiries may be deleted periodically if no ongoing relationship exists.</li>
            </ul>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              Information that is no longer required is securely deleted or destroyed.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              8. Website & Cookies
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              The website may use essential cookies and analytics tools to improve
              website performance, reliability and user experience.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              No sensitive personal information is intentionally collected through cookies.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              9. Your Rights
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              Under UK GDPR you have rights including:
            </p>

            <ul class="mt-4 list-disc space-y-3 pl-6">
              <li>The right to access personal information we hold about you</li>
              <li>The right to correct inaccurate information</li>
              <li>The right to request deletion where appropriate</li>
              <li>The right to restrict or object to processing</li>
              <li>The right to withdraw consent where consent is used</li>
              <li>The right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner’s Office (ICO)</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              10. Security
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              We take reasonable technical and organisational measures to protect personal
              information against unauthorised access, loss, misuse or disclosure.
            </p>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              Access to sensitive information is restricted to authorised club officials where required.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white">
              11. Contact
            </h2>

            <p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed">
              Questions regarding this policy or requests relating to personal data can
              be submitted through the club contact page.
            </p>
          </section>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>